  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite having no recorded citations or online discussions, \"The Tacit Dimension\" published by Leuven University Press in 2021 shows evidence of a strong commercial linkage, suggesting a potential interest in its themes within industry contexts.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Published in 2021 by Leuven University Press, \"The Tacit Dimension\" has not yet recorded any citations or online discussions across platforms like Wikipedia and Reddit. Nevertheless, the book's notable commercial linkage, indicated by its presence on Amazon and Goodreads, suggests a potential interest in its themes outside academic circles. This commercial relationship, with a strength rating of 0.9, infers that the book may resonate with broader audiences interested in its subject matter.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The book demonstrates a commitment to sustainability and policy relevance, as evidenced by its association with one of the Sustainable Development Goals. This connection provides a framework within which the themes presented in the book can be discussed and evaluated in practical contexts, indicating that readers may find the content applicable in real-world scenarios.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">While the scholarly uptake is currently modest, with a strength rating of 0.45, it points to an emerging interest that could develop as the relevance of the discussed themes becomes more pronounced in academic and professional discourse. This gradual increase in interest may reflect a potential for future citations, as foundational ideas often take time to gain traction in scholarly settings.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Overall, while the current data does not reflect extensive academic engagement or public discourse, the existing commercial interests and relevant thematic connections can provide a fertile ground for future exploration and dissemination of the work's ideas. The evolution of interest may soon transform \"The Tacit Dimension\" into a significant reference point within its field.</p>",
